  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(47) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "There was then no king in Edom.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—This notice is apparently connected with the following verses; for Ezion-geber is a seaport of the Edomite territory. Whatever may have been the influence of Hadad in the last days of Solomon (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Kings 11:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), Edom does not seem to have regained independence till the time of Jehoram, son of Jehoshaphat (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Chronicles 21:8-10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); although in the confederacy against Jehoshaphat, those “of Mount Seir” are included with the Moabites and Ammonites (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Chronicles 20:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Chronicles 20:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The “king of Edom,” of 2 Kings 3, who is evidently a subject ally, not regarded in consultation (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Kings 22:6-9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), must be “the deputy” of this passage.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
